name: GMP synthase (glutamine-hydrolysing)
classes: Carbon-nitrogen ligases with glutamine as amido-N-donor
reaction: ATP + XMP + L-glutamine + H2O = AMP + diphosphate + GMP + L-glutamate (overall reaction) [RN:R01231]; (1a) L-glutamine + H2O = L-glutamate + NH3 [RN:R00256]; (1b) ATP + XMP + NH3 = AMP + diphosphate + GMP [RN:R01230]
comment: Involved in the de novo biosynthesis of guanosine nucleotides. An N-terminal glutaminase domain binds L-glutamine and generates ammonia, which is transferred by a substrate-protective tunnel to the ATP-pyrophosphatase domain. The enzyme can catalyse the second reaction alone in the presence of ammonia.
